\subsection{Stuff about efficiencies}
%++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Strictly speaking, the \enaex{} efficiencies of a lamp
are evaluated between the final and useful stages of the energy conversion chain
(where light \enaex{} exist),
prior to the \emph{energy service} stage
(where illumination exists).
Both
%
\begin{enumerate*}[label={(\alph*)}]

  \item the \enaex{} of light and

  \item the \enaex{} efficiency of lamps

\end{enumerate*}
%
are independent of the energy service provided by the lamp.



